    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="361"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/361a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-12">June 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1521. Please inform Swiss Foreign Office and ask that Swiss Minister and Grew,
                    Tokyo, be also informed Department regrets state departure exchange vessel <hi
                        rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> delayed account of failure receive Japanese
                    list American nationals coming from China and because <pb facs="0444" n="432"
                        xml:id="pg_432"/> Japanese Government refused give safe conduct <hi
                        rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> until June 16. Hope these difficulties will be
                    settled and vessel will proceed on June 17.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
